column1: this day gained its name from the assasination of the fearless mirabal sisters. these 3 sisters opposed the dominican dictator rafael trujillo. the assassinations labelled the sisters as ""symbols of both popular and feminist resistance"". minerva the 3rd of the 4 sisters studied law but was denied a license to practice because she declined sexual advances from rafael trujillo. the #metoo campaign is made up of women like minerva who speak up about men in powerful positions using their power to make sexual advances on women. this is a struggle we still face today. .
the importance of this day is to raise awarenesss of rape
column2: domestic violence and other violent acts against women. the aim of this day is to also highlight that these issues are often hidden.

column1: ;metto questa foto che piace tanto roger perché è da stamattina che mi scrivete direct come mai io non abbia postato ancora nulla per la giornata contro la violenza sulle donne . ecco , trovo che istituire una giornata sia abbastanza ingenuo . non per la `` ricorrenza '' sé , che potrebbe essere impoante , perché trovo che il problema sia troppo grande per parlarne solo un giorno l'anno . questa giornata è per chi ? per chi scrive `` una donna non si tocca neanche con un fiore '' e poi gioisce quando un immigrato muore mare ? per chi dice che ogni donna dovrebbe essere libera e poi critica una gon na coa , un tanga , un vestito scollato ? per gli uomini che `` non mi azzarderei mai picchiare la mia ragazza '' poi le impediscono di vivere la propria vita come crede , la umiliano , pensando che il rispetto si limiti far del male fisicamente ? e poi , cosa serve una giornata quando ad oggi il 31,5 % delle donne italiane ha subìto violenza fisica e sessuale e solo l'11 % denuncia ? cosa serve se lo stato non protegge , se la burocrazia è infinita , se le forze dell'ordine non intervengono se non quando ormai non c'è più nulla da fare ? per ricordare le donne uccise , maltrattate , violentate ? loro non hanno bisogno di essere ricordate di avere giustizia , perché questo modo le prossime si convinceranno che qualcuno le tutelerà , che non è colpa loro , che possono uscirne , che possono parlare senza vergogna . la prima volta che ho parlato la ricordo ancora , avevo 15 anni , e descrissi chi di dovere il mio disagio . secondo lui era `` solo qualche battutina '' . quante volte mi sono detta che se solo mi avesse dato retta e fosse intervenuto tempo , probabilmente non avrei ferite profonde addosso . e non avete idea delle vittime collaterali di cui nessuno parla neanche oggi , ad esempio dei figli senza una mamma che si poeranno dietro un trauma , e che non avranno l'appoggio , tantomeno economico , di nessuno . ecco , quest'anno dedico il 25 novembre alle vittime collaterali , compreso roger , che con pazienza ha accettato e consolato ogni complesso e terrore , pur meritando come chiunque una persona emotivamente stabile accan noto . odiate la violenza ogni giorno . ;[('metto'

column1: 137230;instagram;2018-11-25 20:29:57;FALSE;"today millions of ppl around the world unite to #orangetheworld for the international day for the elimination of violence against women (orange symbolizes a brighter future of world free of violence against women & girls.) violence against women & girls (vawg) is widely unreported globally bc speaking up can have fatal consequences. the #metoo movement hasn’t reached many countries bc many women live outside the limelight & media headlines
column4: & shame. we use the hashtag #hearmetoo to raise awareness for survivors & activists that we don’t hear from on social media.

column1: ✔️ 1 in 3 women & girls experience physical or sexual violence
column2: most often by an intimate partner

column1: ✔️ 603mil women live in countries where domestic violence isn’t considered a crime (that’s larger than the population of the us
✔️ marital rape isn’t considered a crime in 35 countries
✔️ 750mil women alive today were married before their 18th bday
✔️ 200mil women alive today have undergone female genital mutilation (fgm)
✔️ 1 in 2 women killed worldwide are killed by their partners or family (vs. 1 in 20 men)
this is not ok ppl. it is all of our responsibility not only to stand in solidarity w women worldwide
column2: but also to intensify our efforts to find solutions & measures to end one of the most prevalent human rights violations in the world. when it comes to vawg
column3: all of us have a story to tell & we all can be supporters
column5: and/or activists. if u witness physical/sexual/psychological violence (it often happens in public) - say something. drop a below 🧡✊🏽in solidarity & tag others 2 spread the word.

column1: 137309;instagram;2018-11-25 21:13:12;FALSE;i wanted to share some pics from thanksgiving
column2: and share a little bit about my experience.  last year on thanksgiving i started my journey with a liquid diet
column3: slowly i was able to transition to food. this year on thanksgiving i had a little bit of everything that i wanted
column4: i didn't feel deprived at all. my portions were very small and i ended up eating two different times to get to taste it all. it was delicious and i want everyone to know you're only limited by yourself so even though i had small plates i still enjoyed a protein coffee and a rich chocolate shake to end off the night. my mission is to encourage others to #bethebestversionofyou my holiday giveaway will start very soon and i would love to have a bunch of you enter. #vsggirl #vsgjourney #followmenow #weightlossdiary #weightlosstory #onmyway #fatgirl #gettinghealthy #wlsjourney #onepoundatatime #onmywaytohealthy #insideandout #wantoinspire #bethechange #methemoglobinemia #mentalhealth #selflove #enough #mommyisback #effyourbeautystandards #metoo;;en;#bethebestversionofyou

column2: even if it makes you feel uncomfortable or stand out; - when you speak up against a wrong

column4: “bitchy” or “arrogant”. do it anyway! every wrong can be made right
column5: even if only by one person
column6: no matter how hard the path. do it anyway
column7: because it is the right thing to do and this changes the world.

column1: 137342;instagram;2018-11-25 21:30:02;FALSE;"hoy es 25 de noviembre. el día que hice esta foto era 18 de octubre. iba en bus de vuelta de clase y me gustó tanto el cielo que me baje dos paradas antes para poder fotografiarlo. hacía tanto que no levantaba la cabeza... ese día me había instalado unas alas en los tobillos para recordarme siempre que nadie tiene ningún derecho a prohibirme nada (mucho menos volar). después de hacer la foto me fui a bailar swing y estuve más de una hora charlando con un leader desconocido después de que me diera las gracias por ser su follower. me sentí tan bien volando libre y alto... pero de vuelta a casa sentí mucho miedo. sentí mucho miedo porque a alguien a quien no puedo denominar hombre
column4: ser violento y seguir haciéndome llorar como empezó a hacerme llorar un año atrás. no me pegó nunca
column6: pero hay formas de violencia igual de terribles que hacen temer por la vida propia al mismo nivel. hoy

column1: 137344;instagram;2018-11-25 21:31:01;FALSE;"a preview (this is just a quick snapshot & not a final work) of a new series that i've been working on with the working titles ""stolen flowers"" & ""flowers from homes"". what is your preferred title for this series?
i started this series to help engage my mind and body in learning to walk again. first in a rehabilitation centre
column2: and then back at home - starting with walking just past one house and back
column3: and now up to 5km at a time. sometimes i can manage walking my wonder dog sebastian ❤. thinking about why i started the series and why i titled it stolen flowers is related to the #metoo hashtag that went viral earlier in the year. my past has been littered with damaging
column4: secretive and painful events starting at an innocent and sheltered version of me at 16yo. when i first tried to speak out about what had happened to me to a psychologist and psychiatrist
column6: pain and inability to process the events as being a drug user & at the time i felt a huge betrayal of privacy as they shared this with my then school and my parents. the experience further damaged my soul and belief in the medical system. it took a long time to trust a psychologist
column7: men and those close to me
column8: let alone share snippets of these painful events.

column1: flowers have long been metaphors for innocence
column2: sexuality and loss of innocence. sometimes the act of ripping or cutting a flower from its plant is a deflowering
column4: a cause of its inability to play a part in the plants future reproduction - a crack in the lifecycle.

column5: unadulterated joy in photographing these small natural miracles
column6: having their scent pervade a room
column7: and carefully arranging them to be lifted up as life symbols.

column1: i hope you enjoy this series - i have a few working photos to share while i'm in post-production of this series.

column1: 137366;instagram;2018-11-25 21:48:18;FALSE;"🔞چرا باید هوش جنسی خود را افزایش دهیم🔞
💯 زنان و مردان به شیوه‌های مختلف مورد خشونت و سوء استفاده قرار می‌گیرند؛ از آزار و خشونت فیزیکی گرفته تا سوء استفاده مالی، آزار جنسی، قاچاق، خشونت علیه سالمندان و سوء استفاده احساسی و کلامی.
🔮 از جمله سوء استفاده‌های جنسی اینکه زن را مجبور به انجام رفتاری جنسی خلاف خواست او بکنند یا او را در زمانی که موافق نیست، مجبور به رابطۀ جنسی یا بارداری کنند.
🔮 تبعیض‌های قانونی، صدور احکام غیرانسانی همچون سنگسار، ازدواج اجباری، ازدواج در زیر سن قانونی، ختنۀ دختران، بارداری آنها در کودکی
🔮 نادیده گرفتن سالمندان و نیازهایشان (مانند محروم کردن آنها از غذا و مراقبتهای بهداشتی در خانه، مراکز مراقبت یا مکان های عمومی

🔮 توهین کردن، ترساندن، منزوی کردن، تلاش برای کنترل کردن، تکرار رفتارهای حسادت آمیز، محروم کردن زن از دیدن دوستان و اعضای خانوادۀ خود، تلاش برای محروم کردن زن از ادامۀ کار یا تحصیل، جلوگیری از رفتن زن به دکتر، تهدید کردن و تصمیم گرفتن به جای زن.
💯 افزایش هوش جنسی مردان و زنان تاثیر مستقیمی بر کاهش خشونت علیه زنان دارد و شامل موارد زیر میشود:
۱- افزایش آگاهی‌های خانواده‌ها به ‌ویژه در جوامع کمتر توسعه یافته
۲- مبارزه با خشونت علیه دختران در مدارس؛ پیگیری خانواده‌ها و گروه‌های مدافع حقوق بشر
۳- کمک به زنان و دختران برای گزارش دادن خشونت‌های خانگی (کمپین "" #metoo "" یکساله شد)
۴- گوش دادن به سخنان زنان و دختران قربانی خشونتهای جنسی
۵- استفاده از شبکه‌های اجتماعی برای طرح تجربه‌های تلخ خشونتهای جنسی
۶- تلاش برای امن کردن مسیر رفت و آمد دختران به مدرسه
۷- پسران و مردان جوان را تبدیل به عاملان تغییر کنید
♀ خشونت‌ها علیه زنان به هر شکلی که انجام شود، می‌تواند برای مدتی طولانی پیامدهای منفی فیزیکی یا احساسی به همراه داشته باشد.

'FW'), ('``', '``'), ('یکساله', 'JJ'), ('شد', 'NN'), ('.', '.'), ('r_saidehmasafi', 'NN'), ('قوق_بشر', 'NN')];🔞چرا باید هوش جنسی خود را افزایش دهیم🔞 ه_به_خشونت_علیه_زنان نیا_را_نارنجی_کن 💯 زنان و مردان به شیوه‌های مختلف مورد خشونت و سوء استفاده قرار می‌گیرند؛ از آزار و خشونت فیزیکی گرفته تا سوء استفاده مالی، آزار جنسی، قاچاق، خشونت علیه سالمندان و سوء استفاده احساسی و کلامی . 🔮 از جمله سوء استفاده‌های جنسی اینکه زن را مجبور به انجام رفتاری جنسی خلاف خواست او بکنند یا او را در زمانی که موافق نیست، مجبور به رابطۀ جنسی یا بارداری کنند . 🔮 تبعیض‌های قانونی، صدور احکام غیرانسانی همچون سنگسار، ازدواج اجباری، ازدواج در زیر سن قانونی، ختنۀ دختران، بارداری آنها در کودکی 🔮 نادیده گرفتن سالمندان و نیازهایشان ( مانند محروم کردن آنها از غذا و مراقبتهای بهداشتی در خانه، مراکز مراقبت یا مکان های عمومی 🔮 توهین کردن، ترساندن، منزوی کردن، تلاش برای کنترل کردن، تکرار رفتارهای حسادت آمیز، محروم کردن زن از دیدن دوستان و اعضای خانوادۀ خود، تلاش برای محروم کردن زن از ادامۀ کار یا تحصیل، جلوگیری از رفتن زن به دکتر، تهدید کردن و تصمیم گرفتن به جای زن . 💯 افزایش هوش جنسی مردان و زنان تاثیر مستقیمی بر کاهش خشونت علیه زنان دارد و شامل موارد زیر میشود : ۱- افزایش آگاهی‌های خانواده‌ها به ‌ویژه در جوامع کمتر توسعه یافته ۲- مبارزه با خشونت علیه دختران در مدارس؛ پیگیری خانواده‌ها و گروه‌های مدافع حقوق بشر ۳- کمک به زنان و دختران برای گزارش دادن خشونت‌های خانگی ( کمپین `` `` یکساله شد ) ۴- گوش دادن به سخنان زنان و دختران قربانی خشونتهای جنسی ۵- استفاده از شبکه‌های اجتماعی برای طرح تجربه‌های تلخ خشونتهای جنسی ۶- تلاش برای امن کردن مسیر رفت و آمد دختران به مدرسه ۷- پسران و مردان جوان را تبدیل به عاملان تغییر کنید ♀ خشونت‌ها علیه زنان به هر شکلی که انجام شود، می‌تواند برای مدتی طولانی پیامدهای منفی فیزیکی یا احساسی به همراه داشته باشد . 💡 کمپین `` metoo `` یکساله شد . r_saidehmasafi came back to knock on my door.
will never let you be free.
with all myself. with all my body.
forgiving doesn't have to mean forgetting.
going on doesn't have to mean accepting.
i built myself a pair of wings and

column2: you say #metoo recently i have recovered my life from complex ptsd and now as a mental health warrior i understand the workings of the mentally ill. i dont make it easy for myself by speaking without a filter but i wouldn't have it any other way. last night i engaged with my parentals only to again be met with hostility aggression and coercion for forging my own path. it seems no amount of explanation or sincerity can get through to some folk that mental illness is justified resentments
column3: entitlement to express angry points of view or an understanding that what you believe to be right or even the law deems to be right is in fact a post marked by time and an evolving universe.

column1: i've been blamed a lot for making people so angry they get violent. you can blame me all you wish throwing punches cause someone doesnt do what you will them to is #mentalillness as is manipulating and distorting the truth to maintain a fixed perspective in which you see yourself.
the human condition is wonderfully awkward and ridiculous if you embrace it and live truthfully you will be rewarded with elation and good vibrations.

column1: 137483;instagram;2018-11-25 23:29:31;FALSE;"this weekend i had the opportunity to reconnect with ann and konstantinos! if you've read my book you will remember them from chapter 4!

thank you for loving me when i wasn't sure how to love myself!

column1: 137484;instagram;2018-11-25 23:30:06;FALSE;"健康って素晴らしいですよね😉

column7: いくつご存知でした😅💦❓ まぁ、スポーツ界の用語が目立ちますよね〜🤔 平昌オリンピックが確か2月でしたから、[そだね〜]なんかは今言う人はいないですけどね〜🙄 流行語がすぐに忘れられてしまうんは最近の特徴ちゃいますかね🤔❓ まぁ、1台のテレビ📺を家族で見たりとか、昔のドリフターズとかみたいな世代超えた人気タレントがいたりした時代が終わって、若い人から高齢者の方まで認める流行語って少なくなってるんでしょうね〜😩💦 あと、なんかドラマとかcmのセリフの流行語って減った気ィしますね〜🤔 メディアが流行語を創造すり力も衰えてるんですかね🙄❓ いずれにしても、今年の大賞が何が選ばれるんか、色々な意味で楽しみですね〜😄 今週も宜しくお願いします✨😄🍂🍁 #ジョギングコース沿道の景色をパチリ📸#北摂を走る#朝焼け#朝焼けの空#新語・流行語大賞#健康って素晴らしいですよね😉仁和令子さん";;en;#ジョギングコース沿道の景色をパチリ📸#北摂を走る#朝焼け#朝焼けの空#新語・流行語大賞#健康って素晴らしいですよね😉仁和令子さん;;;;;0;;hidede_dede;hidededede…;;0;False;0;0;0;10;https://instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/vp/81cdc8d463861793ed164f3f4a9a1bb0/5D0369EE/t51.2885-15/e35/45629379_2238042716442086_5386634981207031016_n.jpg?_nc_ht=instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net;0;FALSE;FALSE;FALSE;english;"健康って素晴らしいですよね😉

column1: we hear a lot of narratives about cases of #domesticviolence
one says to us “i understand why he beats me
column2: all i do is stay at home and no work even though i take care of the children
column3: because i have no money to contribute to take care of all of us in the house” - this throws up issues of #economicempowerment for women. still
column4: it fails to justify why any man should raise his hand against his wife and mother of their children. -

column1: there is a lot of work to be done to #endviolenceagainstwomen

column2: don’t be silent. you can be a #sisterskeeper. whatever you do
column3: don’t be silent when you witness any case of #violence against women because #womenmatter and #womensrightsarehumanrights -

column1: 137519;instagram;2018-11-26 00:31:22;FALSE;"today is the un’s international day for the elimination of violence against women #vaw. what does that mean? it means that today is a day to recognize that #vaw is a widespread issue that goes largely unreported around the world because of silence

the patients borrows from my own life story and my mission with this short is to help create a dialogue about how violence against women manifests — for me it was intimate partner violence (ipv) and the difficult aspects that title encompasses. let’s break this cycle of violence and end the stigma. if we talk about it
on this day of taking action around the world

column1: 137560;instagram;2018-11-26 01:29:21;FALSE;"“i would like to share with you something that happened almost 40 years ago. it was not the catcalling i remember so much but the reaction from my dad.

the 1st time i got catcalled i just started working in nyc in 1979.  i was walking to work and got catcalled by several men.  this type of thing did not happen in the small town i grew up in and i was confused by it all.  it made me feel kinda creepy and anxious...but i was not sure why.

that night at dinner i told my dad what happened.  i asked him why did men do that?  he told me i should take it as a complement.  he said it meant they thought i was ""pretty"". i knew that was not the reason.  i still had no idea the real reason was why these men called ""at me"". and they were men- not teens.  they had to be my dad's age or older.
my dad's mannerism told me that the subject was now closed.
i remember thinking yuck...those men were disgusting.  i was left as a 19 year old to run this gauntlet with no real advice

column1: ;la violencia de género es una causa de desplazamiento forzado afecta paicularmente mujeres refugiadas . este 25 de noviembre es el día internacional de la eliminación de la violencia contra la mujer , comienza la campaña de los 6díasdeactivismo . hasta el 10 de diciembre , día de los derechos humanos , serán impulsadas acciones para poner fin la violencia contra las mujeres las niñas en todo el mundo . la campaña internacional se originó desde el women 's global leadership institute con la coordinación del center women 's global leadership en 1991. en los últimos años , las voces de sobrevivientes activistas , mediante campañas como la de entre otras , han ido gado un protagonismo que ya puede seguir siendo ignorado . el tema de activismo mundial de la campaña únete de este año es scúchametambién con este lema / hashtag se anima las personas celebrar eventos con movimientos de mujeres locales , nacionales , regionales mundiales , defensoras defensores de sobrevivientes de los derechos humanos de las mujeres , crear opounidades para el diálogo entre activistas , personas encargadas de formular políticas el público . al igual que en años anteriores , el color naranja será el elemento clave unificador de todas las actividades , los edificios lugares emblemáticos se iluminarán decorarán con este color para atraer la atención mundial hacia la iniciativa . ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ 📷 : cuenta de twitter cnursuramerica ujeres 6diasdeactivismo 6dayscampaign2018 scúchametambién undonaranja odospeenecemos etoo onlosrefugiados ithrefugees efugees efugiados cnur nhcr cnurvenezuela efugeeswelcome ;[('la'

column1: 137566;instagram;2018-11-26 01:31:50;FALSE;"*trigger warning* (my story of surviving rape) my name is mikayla & i am 17 years old. one year ago
column5: multiple times. my ex boyfriend decided to look past my words
column6: they went into one ear & out the other. consent was far out of his mind. a little while after
column7: i thought i was pregnant-i’ve never been so scared. i kept this inside for a whole year
column9: i didn’t want to believe this actually happened to me. the ptsd got bad
column10: i had to let someone know-my therapist. she has helped me learn how to cope with the flashbacks & nightmares. to come to the terms that i am not only a victim of rape;i am a survivor. if you or anyone you know is facing this-as hard as it is to come to terms with it-you need to tell someone. you do not have to keep it inside. you do not have to let it destroy you. you are a survivor. you are strong. you will get through this. you are not alone
column11: if you feel like you have nobody to go to-please call the hotline provided in this post or dm me. millions of people have to go through this & nobody should have to. my clothes do not determine my consent-her clothes do not determine her consent-his consent-their consent-nobody’s consent. no means no. yes means only one thing- freely given consent! #metoo #metoomovement #triggerwarning #nomeansno #consent #survivor #mystory #ptsd #tellsomeone #speakup #hotline #youareasurvivor #youarestrong #youwillgetthroughthis #hopetoinspire";;en;#metoo

column1: a very good friend of mine made this amazing painting. we always spend money on clothes and technology
column2: fancy beauty products and other such things.

column1: but i saw this painting and it really got to me. especially with the current work i have been doing back home. this painting
column2: i can't describe it in words. mainly because i am not so good at describing things. but i loved it. and i made my first ever art purchase. it made me realise that there are so many amazing artists out there trying to sell their work and we don't seem to make an attempt to buy it. i can't wait to get home and hang this on the wall..and to remind me of the work. i realised it's worth spending money to own a piece of art that gives some mental peace. no matter where i am i know this painting will always be there.

column1: 137635;instagram;2018-11-26 03:32:33;FALSE;"please know that no matter what you are going through right now - you are not alone. people are so good at hiding the hard trials they are going through. what ends up happening is we feel alone and like no one else would understand. but the truth is that everyone is going through hard battles we cannot see on the surface
column2: & we were never made to go through this alone. we were never made to put on a mask of happiness when feeling like our life is falling apart. we’re screaming on the inside for someone to help. we need to stop looking at the surface level things and go beneath the surface to the precious soul that lies beneath. even just a kind word or a smile goes a long way. you never know what people are going through - so be kind and be genuine always.💞dear friend
column3: please know that you are never alone in this fight. i designed the bracelet to be multi colored to remind us that though our struggles are different - they are actually very much the same. our struggles can bring us closer together. please message me right now if you need help or need someone to talk to! **15% of your purchase is donated to the american foundation for suicide prevention @afspnational or to write love on her arms @twloha 🦋if you have something specifically you
column5: is struggling with & you would rather donate there please message me and i would be happy to donate there. hope you all have a wonderful and beautiful week!

column1: 137650;instagram;2018-11-26 04:19:22;FALSE;"kekerasan seksual yang dialami seseorang memiliki berbagai macam dampak negatif hingga mempengaruhi kualitas hidup korban. dampak ini mencakup segi fisik

column2: upaya penanganan dan perlindungan korban masih belum sebanding dengan beratnya dampak yg dialami. rancangan undang-undang penghapusan kekerasan seksual menjadi bagian dari upaya penguatan hukum yang sedang diperjuangkan untuk disahkan sebagai bentuk pencegahan dan penanggulangan kasus kekerasan seksual di indonesia.
aliansi satu visi sebagai aliansi yg mendukung pemenuhan hksr berupaya untuk meningkatkan kepedulian masyarakat terkait kekerasan seksual yang berdampak besar pada kesejahteraan dan kesehatan mental.
kami kembali menjadi mitra festival @enambelasffest dan mengadakan pemutaran film serta diskusi interaktif terkait kekerasan seksual. harapannya
column3: dengan meningkatknya kesadaran masyarakat dan pemangku kepentingan akan kekerasan seksual
column4: maka dapat mendorong terciptanya peraturan yang berpihak pada korban  dan mewujudkan masyarakat yang anti kekerasan.

column1: my biggest fear and inhibitor in coming forward about being sexually assaulted was not being believed. and even though i saw it coming
column2: it didn't make it hurt any less when it inevitably happened.

column1: this thanksgiving someone that is very close to me in my life doubted the validity of my trauma as well as the effect that it has had on my life. and despite the fact that i have been doubted and victim blamed more times than i can count in the past year
column2: i just broke. i am talking full-blown panic attack meltdown hysterical screaming and crying. it was honestly the most severe my flashbacks have ever been to the moments right after i was raped. walking outside in my front lawn in the cold felt and looked exactly like walking to the hospital that freezing december morning for rape kit. after more than an hour of being in hysterics my eyes were swollen
column4: and i was afraid that i may somehow never get it together. this was honestly a breakdown that was a year in the making. it was as if i cried all of the tears about what happened to me all at once.

column1: i am exhausted and tired of having to comfort the people in my life for what happened to me. i understand there is secondary trauma in being close with someone who has been attacked
column3: i need people to be there for me. and it is hard to accept that the people that i want to be there for me may not actually be capable of doing so.

column1: 137659;instagram;2018-11-26 04:30:11;FALSE;"feeling grateful. this weekend i got to facilitate an ecstatic dance (which wonderfully and spontaneously erupted into group singing as well)
column3: have dinner with a dear friend
column4: go to an amazing kirtan with family
column5: go to psychoanalysis (what can i say
column6: i grew up on the couch)
column7: facilitate my women’s sacred circle @homepym with women i have worked with for many years in which i get to teach what i love to teach (i.e. mysticism
column11: cuddle lots with ananda and finish the weekend with a “let’s get sh**t done” meeting for the me too: a time to heal movement i launched last spring with tara elliot @homepym (stay tuned for an amazing spring line up of healing and empowering events that are for  all genders; so many awesome professionals in our community are offering free seminars and workshops this spring! more info soon!) usually
column12: i just plug along. i rarely ever stop to be proud of myself or reflect on my efforts or contributions. but nor do i stop to shame myself or say im not doing enough. i just keep doing what the next apparent thing to be done seems to be.

column1: but today i am happy to pat myself on the back and say
column2: “you’ve caused a lot of drama in your life time lady. but you’ve also done a lot of good. and i believe in who you are.“ may you all find the courage and grace to do the same for yourself
column3: especially my fellow over-workers and overachievers out there.

column1: i am scared while walking in day time.
i am scared while walking in night on roads.
i am scared when some people see me when i wait for trains.
i am scared when someone walks beside me.
i am scared when i meet some relatives and they see me like they checking me out.
i am scared when driving my scooter. suddenly someone followed me.
i feel scared when shopkeepers touch my hand while giving or taking money.
i am scared so much time that now i don't feel freedom. i don't know what is freedom. i don't know how to breathe with peace.
you know what.....now i feel scare of smiling

the clean and pure image of a saint
who works at ngos in the day
which they carry in their hearts
walking on the paths of active molesters
carrying blood and honour of women
on their hands to sell in the markets
which they are the evil bosses of.
i have been at the highest level of tortured
who only knew how to suck out the life
of them who once had given them one.
with men who i once trusted
staring at me with eyes wide opened
gaping and drooling over the skin
and pretend like it happened unknowingly
who do you think are you fooling?
it's not the first time with us.
i have seen extreme levels of lunacy
who stalk young girls and catch them alone
sucking out the belief of humanity
which was once fed into them.
along with what's little left of them
looking at photos and idols of goddesses
who they were taught to worship once.
which could possibly quench their undying thirst
supposedly every hole they found out there.
how if humanity was counted in currency
they were the poorest beggars of them all.
and it has exceeded all bars
there is no escape from accepting the truth
where even dogs aren't safe anymore.

column1: 137724;instagram;2018-11-26 06:36:11;FALSE;"i received the message to the left on instagram
column3: i don’t check my messages a lot
column4: because i just saw it. i usually receive such sweet messages so my jaw dropped to the floor when i came across this one. truthfully
column6: i laughed out loud. it sounded so falsely shakespearean
column8: who talks like that? then i got angry
column9: “how dare this person who doesn’t even know me randomly send me a nasty
column11: ignorant bigoted message because i’m married to someone who is not black!” then i wondered if he sent black men similar messages or did he just feel more comfortable harassing a woman. after those emotions
column12: i just felt sad for this man. sad that he has to walk around with the heavy load of hate. and then i thought about sgt. jan pietrzak
column13: usmc and quiana faye jenkins- pietrzak
column14: the couple to the right. an interracial couple who was randomly brought to my attention about 10 years ago
column15: by a stranger on the internet. quiana and jan were brutally murdered in california on october 14
column16: 2008 (a month before michael and i got married) by four men who knew them. the murder was called a robbery by officials. but
column17: their families stand by the fact that they believe it was a racially motivated hate crime
column18: motivated by jealousy. i have silently mourned this couple for ten years. and i stand behind what their families believe. interracial couple have been dealing with hate for so long. it’s still happening. everywhere. to learn more about this beautiful couple
column19: please take some time to visit the facebook page dedicated to them. search - in loving memory of sgt. jan pietrzak

column1: 137726;instagram;2018-11-26 06:37:39;FALSE;"i’ve been questioned why i decided to write a memoir about a near death experience and cover an episode sexual assault while living in south korea. i had to make sense of these two life-changing moments. that’s why. most people must make sense of wild changes in their own lives and work toward greater peace. i wanted to share a healing journey and what specifically worked. i wanted to show how spiritual insights from the other side can heal and unravel anything that happens to us in physical form. if you look to the other side
i understand people’s questions about why guides and angels didn’t protect me from a stalker or a rapist.  there are lots of answers to this question---my personality type is an open friendly
column4: more creative than analytical type of personality.  it has taken me years to learn self-defense
column6: and deeper analysis of societal structures.  i was twenty-two and blown open with love from the other side. i didn’t pay attention to signs at times and wanted to be young and “normal.” i didn’t hone my intuition in that way. statistically
column7: high numbers of women have been stalked
column9: or harassed. the young are often vulnerable to their society and time. is any tragedy part of their soul plan
column10: or did they simply choose to be born in a dangerous world with some risks?  who can say for certain? there is much spiritual confusion in this world
column11: and it is more important to focus on the individual and societal healing. it is more important to create a safer world than to analyze why something happened on a spiritual level. the only thing that is certain is that we sign up for a temporary ride in physical form. i am passionate about helping people heal quicker. there are so many modalities for healing
column12: and i’ve experienced many miraculous healing in my life. we deserve freedom from trauma. we all deserve beautiful
column13: safe lives. that much i know. .

column1: 137802;instagram;2018-11-26 09:44:07;FALSE;"south korea loves plastic surgery and makeup. some women want to change that.~ntyimes.com
kim ji-yeon knew she wanted plastic surgery when she was 7. for the next 13 years
column2: she destroyed photos of herself until her parents paid for double jaw surgery
column3: a procedure that requires breaking the jaw to realign it.

column1: then ms. kim started to question why she devoted so much — $200 a month and two hours a day
column2: she calculated — to her appearance. she cut her hair short. then she crushed her makeup into pieces.

column3: is one of a growing group of south korean women rebelling against their society’s rigid beauty standards — a push they call “escape the corset.” inspired in part by the global #metoo movement
column4: which has shaken up politics and society in south korea’s deeply patriarchal culture
column5: the women are challenging long-accepted attitudes about plastic surgery and cosmetics in one of the world’s most beauty-obsessed capitals. “misogyny is more extreme in south korea
column6: and the beauty industry has made it worse

column1: beauty is big in south korea. it has the world’s highest rate of cosmetic surgery per capita
column2: and it keeps rising. it has become a destination for nip-and-tuck tourism. the beauty market — cosmetics and facial care products like masks — generated $13 billion in sales last year
column4: making it one of the world’s top 10 beauty markets.

column2: the international day for the elimination of violence against women
column5: the #16daysofactivism against #genderbasedviolence campaign is a time to galvanize action to end violence against women and girls around the world. the international campaign originated from the first women's global leadership institute coordinated by the center for women's global leadership in 1991. for far too long
column7: silence and stigma have allowed violence against women to escalate to pandemic proportions—1 in 3 women worldwide experience gender-based violence. the time for change is here and now. in recent years

through things is to allow them to be. we gotta feel the pain & grief & sorrow & let it pass through us. we don’t have to post on our ex’s wall when we see they have a new supply, we don’t have to punish ourselves bc we can’t force ourselves to be happy joyous & free immediately after coming out of abuse or #addiction. it’s ok. breathe, feel & #letitbe we gotta make room for #peace. #grayrock column2: marked the beginning of the 16 days of activism against gender based violence.

column1: the biggest problem south africa faces is the silence accompanied with this sort of violence.
the shocking truth is that society has normalized abuse. society has desensitized the severity that abuse causes to an individual.

the only solution to this shocking truth is to speak out. more leaders need to stand up and use their voices to encourage victims to speak out. to report their abusers. victims are often left to deal with the pain and trauma in isolation. 34% of children in sa are the victims of sexual violence and physical abuse before they have reach 18 years old. and majority of that 34% is never reported. more everyday people need to stand up for those that cannot stand up for themselves. more mothers need to stand up for their children. more family members need speak out and help those they know are being hurt. more people need to have the guts to speak up for their friends who are being abused.
the more we speak out about this the more aware society will become. awareness is education and education is the most powerful tool to change.
join the me too movement and speak out. .

column1: la campaña 16 días de activismo contra la violencia de género es un momento en el que impulsar acciones para poner fin a la violencia contra las mujeres y las niñas en todo el mundo.

column3: el silencio y el estigma han permitido que la violencia contra las mujeres aumente hasta alcanzar proporciones de pandemia: una de cada tres mujeres en todo el mundo sufre violencia de género.

column1: el momento para el cambio es aquí y ahora.

column2: las voces de sobrevivientes y activistas
column3: mediante campañas como la de #metoo o #yotambién
column8: han ido ganando un protagonismo que ya no puede seguir siendo ignorado.

column1: las y los activistas entienden que si bien los nombres y los contextos pueden variar en función de los distintos lugares geográficos
column2: las mujeres y las niñas de todo el mundo sufren maltratos generalizados y sus historias deben salir a la luz.

column1: por eso el tema de activismo mundial de la campaña únete de este año es: pinta el mundo de naranja: #escúchametambién
al igual que en años anteriores
column2: el color naranja será el elemento clave unificador de todas las actividades
column3: y los edificios y lugares emblemáticos se iluminarán y decorarán con este color para atraer la atención mundial hacia la iniciativa.

become more aware of your inner workings and you will change the world.

column1: the “me too” phenomenon that has erupted in our social media-scape is a wake up call. it demonstrates that sexuality is never expressed in a vacuum; it exists in a power dynamic. for millennia men have been on top. but now masculinity is toxic and the male sex drive is libido non-grata. are we ushering a new age of conservatism or can we move towards a truly ethical sexual liberation? this show put this question and many more around masculinity and sexuality to a group of men who are unapologetic when it comes to the expression of their sexuality.
